worldMap.svg
============

Source : https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:BlankMap-World.svg
        (Polish Wikipedia mirror: https://pl.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plik:BlankMap-World6.svg)
Author : Canuckguy and many others (per Wikimedia file history)
License: Public domain — released by the copyright holder

This SVG is bundled as `worldMap.svg` with one local modification (see
below). Paths are ID'd by ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 lowercase, with extra codes
for disputed territories (e.g. `xk` for Kosovo). Zero transforms, zero
text labels, zero line elements, zero inline fills — clean to style via
our CSS and to mount without per-country bbox transformation tricks.

Local modification: added a small `<g id="ax">` (a tiny path + an r=6
locator circle) for the Åland Islands in the Baltic between Sweden and
Finland, which the source map omitted. This lets the flag map ring and
label Åland like any other microstate. The source is public domain, so
this modified copy remains freely usable.

Used by the flagQuiz Europe-and-beyond contour map feature: per-variant
viewBox crops at runtime focus the same asset on each continent.
